-- Configuration
local MONITOR_SIDE = "top"
local REDSTONE_SIDE = "back"
local CHATBOX_SIDE = "bottom"
local WHITELIST = {"M_CI_HYPE"} -- Fixed nickname
local CHECK_RADIUS = 20
local SECRET_PASSWORD = "open"
local LOG_FILE = "security_log.txt"

-- Peripheral initialization
local playerDetector = peripheral.find("playerDetector")
local monitor = peripheral.find("monitor")
local chatBox = peripheral.find("chatBox")

if monitor then
    monitor.setTextScale(0.5)
end

-- Colors
local colors = {
    green = 32768,
    yellow = 16,
    white = 1,
    red = 16384,
    orange = 4
}

-- State variables
local currentPage = 1
local lastIntruders = {}
local lastTouchTime = 0
local touchCooldown = 0.5
local overrideActive = false
local overrideEndTime = 0
local overrideDuration = 10
local overrideBy = ""

-- Tracking for logging
local playersInZone = {}

function isInWhitelist(username)
    for _, whitelistedName in ipairs(WHITELIST) do
        if whitelistedName == username then
            return true
        end
    end
    return false
end

function logEvent(username, doorOpened, openedBy)
    local timestamp = os.date("%H:%M:%S")
    local status = doorOpened and "was" or "wasn't"
    local logEntry = "Player detected: " .. username .. ", time: " .. timestamp .. 
                    ". Door " .. status .. " opened. Opened by: " .. openedBy
    
    print("Attempting to log: " .. logEntry)
    
    -- Save to file
    local logFile = fs.open(LOG_FILE, "a")
    if logFile then
        logFile.writeLine(logEntry)
        logFile.close()
        print("Successfully logged to file")
    else
        print("ERROR: Failed to open log file for writing")
    end
end

function handleMonitorTouch()
    while true do
        local event, side, x, y = os.pullEvent("monitor_touch")
        local currentTime = os.clock()
        
        if currentTime - lastTouchTime > touchCooldown then
            lastTouchTime = currentTime
            
            if #lastIntruders > 0 then
                currentPage = currentPage + 1
                if currentPage > #lastIntruders then
                    currentPage = 1
                end
                updateDisplay()
            end
        end
    end
end

function handleChat()
    while true do
        local event, username, message, uuid = os.pullEvent("chat")
        print("Chat received from " .. username .. ": " .. message)
        
        if message:lower() == SECRET_PASSWORD then
            local players = playerDetector.getPlayersInRange(CHECK_RADIUS)
            local playerInRange = false
            
            print("Checking players in range for " .. username)
            for _, player in ipairs(players) do
                if player and player.name then -- Added nil check
                    print("Found player: " .. player.name)
                    if player.name == username and isInWhitelist(username) then
                        playerInRange = true
                        break
                    end
                end
            end
            
            if playerInRange then
                overrideActive = true
                overrideEndTime = os.time() + overrideDuration
                overrideBy = username
                
                logEvent(username, true, "secret word")
                
                if chatBox then
                    chatBox.sendMessageToPlayer(username, "Override activated for " .. overrideDuration .. " seconds")
                end
                
                print("Override activated by " .. username)
                updateDisplay()
            else
                print("Access denied for " .. username .. " - not in range or not in whitelist")
                if chatBox then
                    chatBox.sendMessageToPlayer(username, "Access denied")
                end
            end
        end
    end
end

function updateDisplay()
    if not monitor then 
        print("No monitor found")
        return 
    end
    
    monitor.clear()
    local width, height = monitor.getSize()
    
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, 1)
    monitor.setTextColor(colors.white)
    monitor.write("Access Control System")
    
    if overrideActive then
        local timeLeft = overrideEndTime - os.time()
        if timeLeft > 0 then
            monitor.setCursorPos(1, 2)
            monitor.setTextColor(colors.orange)
            monitor.write("OVERRIDE: " .. timeLeft .. "s")
            monitor.setCursorPos(1, 3)
            monitor.write("By: " .. overrideBy)
        else
            overrideActive = false
        end
    end
    
    local doorStatusLine = overrideActive and 4 or 2
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, doorStatusLine)
    
    if #lastIntruders == 0 or overrideActive then
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.green)
        monitor.write("ACCESS GRANTED")
    else
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.red)
        monitor.write("ACCESS DENIED")
    end
    
    local intrudersStartLine = doorStatusLine + 2
    
    if #lastIntruders == 0 then
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, intrudersStartLine)
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.green)
        monitor.write("Area secure")
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, intrudersStartLine + 1)
        monitor.write("No intruders detected")
    else
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, intrudersStartLine)
        if overrideActive then
            monitor.setTextColor(colors.orange)
            monitor.write("Warning: " .. #lastIntruders .. " strangers")
        else
            monitor.setTextColor(colors.yellow)
            monitor.write("Warning: " .. #lastIntruders .. " strangers")
        end
        
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, intrudersStartLine + 1)
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.white)
        monitor.write("Viewing: " .. currentPage .. "/" .. #lastIntruders)
        
        local intruder = lastIntruders[currentPage]
        if intruder then
            monitor.setCursorPos(1, intrudersStartLine + 3)
            monitor.setTextColor(colors.yellow)
            monitor.write("Name: " .. intruder.name)
            monitor.setCursorPos(1, intrudersStartLine + 4)
            monitor.write("Max HP: " .. intruder.maxHealth)
        end
        
        if monitor.isColor() then
            monitor.setCursorPos(1, height)
            monitor.setTextColor(colors.white)
            monitor.write("Touch screen to cycle")
        end
    end
end

function main()
    print("Starting security system...")
    
    -- Create log file with more verbose error handling
    local logFile = fs.open(LOG_FILE, "a")
    if logFile then
        logFile.writeLine("Security System Log - Started: " .. os.date())
        logFile.close()
        print("Log file created/accessed successfully")
    else
        print("ERROR: Could not create or access log file")
    end
    
    -- Initial display update
    updateDisplay()
    
    -- Start listeners
    local parallelFunctions = {}
    
    if monitor and monitor.isColor() then
        table.insert(parallelFunctions, function()
            print("Starting touch listener")
            handleMonitorTouch()
        end)
    end
    
    if chatBox then
        table.insert(parallelFunctions, function()
            print("Starting chat listener")
            handleChat()
        end)
    end
    
    -- Main detection loop
    table.insert(parallelFunctions, function()
        print("Starting main detection loop")
        local previousPlayers = {}
        
        while true do
            local players = playerDetector.getPlayersInRange(CHECK_RADIUS) or {}
            local authorized = false
            local intruders = {}
            local currentPlayers = {}
            
            print("Players in range: " .. #players)
            
            -- Track current players for logging
            for _, player in ipairs(players) do
                if player and player.name then  -- Added nil check
                    print("Processing player: " .. player.name)
                    currentPlayers[player.name] = true
                    
                    if isInWhitelist(player.name) then
                        authorized = true
                        print("Authorized player detected: " .. player.name)
                    else
                        print("Intruder detected: " .. player.name)
                        table.insert(intruders, {
                            name = player.name,
                            maxHealth = math.floor(player.maxHealth or 20)
                        })
                    end
                else
                    print("WARNING: Found player with nil name")
                end
            end
            
            -- Log player entries (only when they first enter)
            for playerName, _ in pairs(currentPlayers) do
                if not previousPlayers[playerName] then
                    print("New player entered zone: " .. playerName)
                    local doorOpened = (authorized and #intruders == 0) or overrideActive
                    local openedBy = overrideActive and "secret word" or "auto"
                    logEvent(playerName, doorOpened, openedBy)
                end
            end
            
            -- Reset page if intruder list changed
            if #intruders ~= #lastIntruders then
                currentPage = 1
            end
            
            lastIntruders = intruders
            previousPlayers = currentPlayers
            
            -- Check if override has expired
            if overrideActive and os.time() > overrideEndTime then
                overrideActive = false
                print("Override expired")
            end
            
            -- Control door
            local shouldOpen = (authorized and #intruders == 0) or overrideActive
            redstone.setOutput(REDSTONE_SIDE, shouldOpen)
            
            -- Update display
            updateDisplay()
            
            os.sleep(0.5)
        end
    end)
    
    -- Run all functions in parallel
    print("Starting parallel execution with " .. #parallelFunctions .. " functions")
    parallel.waitForAny(table.unpack(parallelFunctions))
end

-- Error handling
print("Initializing security system...")
local ok, err = pcall(main)
if not ok then
    print("System error: " .. err)
    if monitor then
        monitor.clear()
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, 1)
        monitor.setTextColor(colors.red)
        monitor.write("SYSTEM ERROR")
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, 2)
        monitor.write(tostring(err))
    end
end

import numpy as np

# ------------------------------------------------------
#  Utility functions
# ------------------------------------------------------

def los_from_az_el(az, el):
    """Convert az/el (radians) to topocentric LOS unit vector."""
    # Local topocentric frame: x = east, y = north, z = up
    x = np.cos(el) * np.sin(az)
    y = np.cos(el) * np.cos(az)
    z = np.sin(el)
    return np.vstack((x, y, z)).T


def quadratic_fit(t, values):
    """Fit a quadratic polynomial to component values vs time."""
    A = np.vstack([t**2, t, np.ones_like(t)]).T
    coeff, *_ = np.linalg.lstsq(A, values, rcond=None)
    return coeff  # a, b, c


def eval_quadratic(coeff, t):
    a, b, c = coeff
    return a * t**2 + b * t + c


def pca_plane_projection(R):
    """
    Fit a plane to the set of 3D points R (Nx3).
    Return projected points and plane normal.
    """
    mean_r = R.mean(axis=0)
    X = R - mean_r
    C = X.T @ X / len(R)
    eigvals, eigvecs = np.linalg.eigh(C)
    # Smallest eigenvalue eigenvector = plane normal
    n = eigvecs[:, np.argmin(eigvals)]
    # project
    proj = R - np.outer((R - mean_r) @ n, n)
    return proj, n


def reject_outliers(residuals, k=3.0):
    """Return boolean mask: True = keep point."""
    med = np.median(residuals)
    mad = np.median(np.abs(residuals - med))
    if mad == 0:
        return np.ones_like(residuals, dtype=bool)
    z = 0.6745 * (residuals - med) / mad
    return np.abs(z) < k


# ------------------------------------------------------
#  Main preprocessing pipeline
# ------------------------------------------------------

def preprocess_for_iod(t, az, el, rho, r_site_eci, el_min_deg=20.0):
    """
    Implements steps 2 ‚Üí 6 from the earlier list.
    Returns: r1, r2, r3 (3 clean ECI position vectors)
    """

    # -------------------------
    # Step 2: Drop low elevation
    # -------------------------
    mask = (el * 180/np.pi) > el_min_deg
    t = t[mask]
    az = az[mask]
    el = el[mask]
    rho = rho[mask]
    r_site_eci = r_site_eci[mask]

    # -------------------------
    # Build raw ECI positions
    # -------------------------
    los = los_from_az_el(az, el)
    R = r_site_eci + rho[:, None] * los   # Nx3

    # -------------------------
    # Step 3: Quadratic fit on each component
    # -------------------------
    t0 = t - t.mean()  # center time for numerical stability

    coeff_x = quadratic_fit(t0, R[:, 0])
    coeff_y = quadratic_fit(t0, R[:, 1])
    coeff_z = quadratic_fit(t0, R[:, 2])

    R_fit = np.column_stack([
        eval_quadratic(coeff_x, t0),
        eval_quadratic(coeff_y, t0),
        eval_quadratic(coeff_z, t0)
    ])

    # -------------------------
    # Step 4: PCA plane projection
    # -------------------------
    R_proj, normal = pca_plane_projection(R_fit)

    # -------------------------
    # Step 5: Outlier rejection
    # -------------------------
    res = np.linalg.norm(R_proj - R_fit, axis=1)
    keep = reject_outliers(res, k=3.0)

    t = t[keep]
    R_proj = R_proj[keep]

    # -------------------------
    # Step 6: Pick 3 clean points around max elevation
    # -------------------------
    # Use the time closest to mid-pass (middle sample)
    mid_idx = len(t) // 2
    t2 = t[mid_idx]

    # Choose t1 and t3 symmetrically by time spacing
    # You may tune dt_window depending on pass length
    dt_window = (t[-1] - t[0]) * 0.25  # quarter-span on each side

    t1 = t2 - dt_window
    t3 = t2 + dt_window

    # interpolate smoothed/proj positions at t1, t2, t3
    def interp_R(t_query):
        return np.column_stack([
            np.interp(t_query, t, R_proj[:, 0]),
            np.interp(t_query, t, R_proj[:, 1]),
            np.interp(t_query, t, R_proj[:, 2])
        ])

    r1 = interp_R(t1)[0]
    r2 = interp_R(t2)[0]
    r3 = interp_R(t3)[0]

    return r1, r2, r3

title: Raycast Gun Template
content:
local currentCamera: Camera = workspace.CurrentCamera
local Debris = game:GetService("Debris")
local player: Player = game:GetService("Players").LocalPlayer
local UIS: UserInputService = game:GetService("UserInputService")
local DAMAGE = 10
local character = player.Character or player.CharacterAdded:Wait()
local tool: Tool = player.Backpack.Tool

local raycastParams: RaycastParams = RaycastParams.new()
raycastParams.FilterDescendantsInstances = { character } -- fill this in yourself

local aiming = false
UIS.InputEnded:Connect(function(input)
   local inputType = input.UserInputType
   if inputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseButton2 then
        aiming = false
    end
end)

UIS.InputBegan:Connect(function(input)
   local inputType = input.UserInputType
   if inputType == Enum.UserInputType.MouseButton2 then
        aiming = true
    end
end)
local MIN_BAD_AIM = 100
local MAX_BAD_AIM = 100
tool.Activated:Connect(function(input)
	local muzzle = tool.Handle
	print("button is down")
	local VIEWPORT_SIZE = currentCamera.ViewportSize / 2 -- current size of the screen -- if you're raycasting multiple times, this will have to be redefined!
	local CAST_LENGTH = 1000 -- distance to raycast

	local x_offset = 0
	local y_offset = 0
	if not aiming then
		x_offset += math.random(-MIN_BAD_AIM, MIN_BAD_AIM)
		y_offset += math.random(-MIN_BAD_AIM, MIN_BAD_AIM)
	end
	local unitRay = currentCamera:ViewportPointToRay(VIEWPORT_SIZE.X + x_offset, VIEWPORT_SIZE.Y + y_offset) -- account for the 36px TopBar inset
	local raycastResult = workspace:Raycast(unitRay.Origin, unitRay.Direction * CAST_LENGTH, raycastParams)

	if raycastResult and raycastResult.Position then -- .Position is the Vector3 (the Hit.Position) of the center of the screen
		local partFound: Instance = raycastResult.Instance
		local distance = (muzzle.Position - raycastResult.Position).Magnitude
		local p = Instance.new("Part")
		p.Anchored = true
		p.CanCollide = false
		p.Parent = workspace
		p.Size = Vector3.new(0.1, 0.1, distance)
		p.CFrame = CFrame.lookAt(muzzle.Position, raycastResult.Position)*CFrame.new(0, 0, -distance/2)
		task.defer(function()
			local transparency = 0
			while transparency ~= 1 do
				p.Transparency += 0.1
				task.wait(0.02)
			end
			Debris:AddItem(p, 0.05)
		end)
		local humanoid = partFound.Parent:WaitForChild("Humanoid", 5)
		if humanoid then
			humanoid.Health -= DAMAGE
		end
	end
end)

title: script_trabalho_empresa
Dungeon Crawler Enemy Class
content:
---------------------------------enemies.py---------------------------------
import pygame
import random
from message import *
from projectile import *


class Enemy(pygame.sprite.Sprite):
    def __init__(self, path, pos, level):
        super().__init__()
        self.path = path
        self.image = pygame.image.load(path)
        self.imagePath = path
        self.rect = self.image.get_rect()
        self.rect.center = pos
        self.heading = None
        self.movement = pygame.math.Vector2(0, 2)
        self.movement.rotate_ip(random.randint(0, 360))
        self.level = level
        self.health = 10
        self.attack_damage = 3
        self.defense = 1
        self.reload = 20
        self.target = None
        self.projectile_cooldown = 180  # 3 seconds at 60fps
        self.projectile_timer = random.randint(0, self.projectile_cooldown)  # staggered firing


    def update(self):
        if pygame.sprite.collide_rect(self, self.level.player) and self.level.player.alive:
            self.target = self.level.player
        else:
            self.target = None
        if self.target is not None:
            self.reload -= 1
            if self.reload == 0:
                self.reload = 60
                self.attack(self.target)
            return
        self.rect.move_ip(self.movement)
        if len(pygame.sprite.spritecollide(self, self.level.walls, False)) >= 1:
            self.movement.rotate_ip(180)
            self.rect.move_ip(self.movement)
            self.movement.rotate_ip(random.randint(0, 360))
        self.projectile_timer = self.projectile_timer - 1
        if self.projectile_timer <= 0:
            self.projectile_timer = self.projectile_cooldown
            self.fire_projectiles()

    def fire_projectiles(self):
        directions = [
            (0, -1),  # up
            (0, 1),   # down
            (-1, 0),  # left
            (1, 0),   # right
        ]
        for dir in directions:
            projectile = Projectile(
                pos=self.rect.center,
                direction=dir,
                speed=4,
                damage=2,
                level=self.level,
                imagepath='images/fireball.gif'
            )
            self.level.projectiles.add(projectile)


    def attack(self, player):
        player.defend(self.attack_damage)

    def defend(self, damage):
        if random.randint(1, 20) > self.defense:
            self.health -= damage
            if self.health <= 0:
                self.kill()
                if len(self.level.enemies) == 0 and not self.level.exit.unlocked:
                    self.level.messages.add(Message("Level Cleared,", (self.rect.centerx, self.rect.centery-30)))
                    self.level.messages.add(Message("Exit Unlocked!", self.rect.center))
                    self.level.exit.unlock()
                return True

title: Compilador NASM
content:
#!/bin/bash

# compila o arquivo no primeiro par√¢metro

arquivo=$1  # esse ser√° o nome do arquivo sem extens√£o, que ser√° o destino final
origem="$arquivo.asm"  # esse √© o arquivo de origem (fonte)
objeto="$arquivo.o"  # esse √© o arquivo objeto intermedi√°rio

# compila o arquivo assembly com nasm
nasm -f elf64 "$origem" -o "$objeto"

if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then  # se der erro ao compilar
    echo "Erro na compila√ß√£o do arquivo $origem"
    exit 1
fi

# linka o arquivo objeto para gerar o execut√°vel final
ld "$objeto" -o "$arquivo"

if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then  # se der erro ao linkar
    echo "Erro ao linkar o arquivo $objeto"
    exit 1
fi

# remove o arquivo objeto intermedi√°rio
rm "$objeto"

if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then  # se der erro ao apagar o arquivo
    echo "Erro ao apagar o arquivo $objeto"
    exit 1
fi

# finaliza com sucesso
echo "Arquivo compilado: $arquivo"
exit 0

-- Functions
local function ModifyTreeHitbox()
    if TreeHitboxEnabled then
        for _, tree in pairs(Workspace:GetDescendants()) do
            if tree:IsA("Model") and (tree.Name:lower():find("tree") or tree:FindFirstChild("TreePart")) then
                for _, part in pairs(tree:GetDescendants()) do
                    if part:IsA("BasePart") then
                        part.Size = Vector3.new(TreeHitboxSize.Width, TreeHitboxSize.Height, TreeHitboxSize.Depth)
                        part.CanCollide = false
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end
end

local function ModifyWeaponHitbox()
    if WeaponHitboxEnabled then
        local Tool = Character:FindFirstChildOfClass("Tool")
        if Tool then
            for _, part in pairs(Tool:GetDescendants()) do
                if part:IsA("BasePart") and part.Name == "Handle" then
                    part.Size = Vector3.new(WeaponHitboxSize.Width, WeaponHitboxSize.Height, WeaponHitboxSize.Depth)
                end
            end
        end
    end
end

local function CreateChestESP()
    if ESPEnabled then
        for _, chest in pairs(Workspace:GetDescendants()) do
            if chest:IsA("Model") and chest:FindFirstChild("ChestPart") or (chest.Name:lower():find("chest") and chest:IsA("Model")) then
                if not chest:FindFirstChild("ChestESP") then
                    local billboard = Instance.new("BillboardGui")
                    billboard.Name = "ChestESP"
                    billboard.Parent = chest
                    billboard.AlwaysOnTop = true
                    billboard.Size = UDim2.new(0, 100, 0, 50)
                    billboard.StudsOffset = Vector3.new(0, 3, 0)
                    
                    local frame = Instance.new("Frame")
                    frame.Parent = billboard
                    frame.Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 1, 0)
                    frame.BackgroundColor3 = ESPColor
                    frame.BackgroundTransparency = 0.5
                    frame.BorderSizePixel = 0
                    
                    local text = Instance.new("TextLabel")
                    text.Parent = frame
                    text.Size = UDim2.new(1, 0, 1, 0)
                    text.BackgroundTransparency = 1
                    text.TextColor3 = Color3.new(1, 1, 1)
                    text.TextScaled = true
                    text.Font = Enum.Font.SourceSansBold
                    text.Text = chest.Name
                end
            end
        end
    end
end

local function AutoCollect()
    if AutoCollectChests then
        spawn(function()
            for _, chest in pairs(Workspace:GetDescendants()) do
                if chest:IsA("Model") and (chest.Name:lower():find("chest") or chest:FindFirstChild("ChestPart")) then
                    if SelectedChest == "All" or chest.Name:find(SelectedChest) then
                        if chest.PrimaryPart or chest:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("BasePart") then
                            local chestPart = chest.PrimaryPart or chest:FindFirstChildWhichIsA("BasePart")
                            if HumanoidRootPart and chestPart then
                                HumanoidRootPart.CFrame = chestPart.CFrame
                                wait(0.3)
                            end
                        end
                    end
                end
            end
        end)
    end
end

-- Character Respawn Handler
Player.CharacterAdded:Connect(function(newCharacter)
    Character = newCharacter
    HumanoidRootPart = Character:WaitForChild("HumanoidRootPart")
    Humanoid = Character:WaitForChild("Humanoid")
end)

-- Anti AFK
if AntiAFK then
    Player.Idled:Connect(function()
        VirtualUser:Button2Down(Vector2.new(0,0), workspace.CurrentCamera.CFrame)
        wait(1)
        VirtualUser:Button2Up(Vector2.new(0,0), workspace.CurrentCamera.CFrame)
    end)
end

-- Main Loop
RunService.RenderStepped:Connect(function()
    pcall(function()
        -- Walk Speed
        if Humanoid and Humanoid.WalkSpeed ~= WalkSpeed then
            Humanoid.WalkSpeed = WalkSpeed
        end
        
        -- Jump Power
        if Humanoid and Humanoid.JumpPower ~= JumpPower then
            Humanoid.JumpPower = JumpPower
        end
        
        -- Spin
        if SpinSpeed > 0 and HumanoidRootPart then
            HumanoidRootPart.CFrame = HumanoidRootPart.CFrame * CFrame.Angles(0, math.rad(SpinSpeed), 0)
        end
        
        -- No Clip
        if NoClip then
            for _, part in pairs(Character:GetDescendants()) do
                if part:IsA("BasePart") then
                    part.CanCollide = false
                end
            end
        end
        
        -- Invisible Tool
        if InvisibleTool then
            local Tool = Character:FindFirstChildOfClass("Tool")
            if Tool then
                for _, part in pairs(Tool:GetDescendants()) do
                    if part:IsA("BasePart") or part:IsA("MeshPart") then
                        part.Transparency = 1
                    end
                end
            end
        end
        
        -- Modify Hitboxes
        ModifyTreeHitbox()
        ModifyWeaponHitbox()
        
        -- Create ESP
        CreateChestESP()
        
        -- Auto Collect
        if AutoCollectChests then
            AutoCollect()
        end
    end)
end)

Rayfield:Notify({
    Title = "Script Loaded!",
    Content = "Cut Trees Script by JayRBLX is ready!",
    Duration = 5,
    Image = 4483362458
})

print("Cut Trees Script by JayRBLX loaded successfully!")
print("YouTube: https://youtube.com/@jayscriptsrblx")
print("Discord: https://discord.gg/KPUPp4m9pJ")

        }
        @keyframes spin { 100% { transform: rotate(360deg); } }

  # Kompressor Frekvens - Lige over kompressoren
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_current_compressor_frequency_eb101
    style:
      top: 74%
      left: 90%

  # Ekspansionsventil (EEV) - Ved timeglasset til venstre
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_eev_percentage
    style:
      top: 74%
      left: 15%

  # Driftsikoner
  # Varmt Vand
  - type: conditional
    conditions:
      - entity: binary_sensor.vvm_500_hot_water_mode
        state: "on"
    elements:
      - type: state-icon
        entity: binary_sensor.vvm_500_hot_water_mode
        style:
          top: 30%
          left: 25%
          transform: scale(2.3)
  # Varme
  - type: conditional
    conditions:
      - entity: binary_sensor.vvm_500_heating_mode
        state: "on"
    elements:
      - type: state-icon
        entity: binary_sensor.vvm_500_heating_mode
        style:
          top: 30%
          left: 25%
          transform: scale(2.3)
  # Afrimning
  - type: conditional
    conditions:
      - entity: binary_sensor.vvm_500_defrost_mode
        state: "on"
    elements:
      - type: state-icon
        entity: binary_sensor.vvm_500_defrost_mode
        style:
          top: 30%
          left: 25%
          transform: scale(2.3)
  # OFF
  - type: conditional
    conditions:
      - entity: binary_sensor.vvm_idle
        state: "on"
    elements:
      - type: state-icon
        entity: binary_sensor.vvm_idle
        style:
          top: 30%
          left: 25%
          transform: scale(2.3)

  # =================================================================
  # ZONE 2: R√òRF√òRING MELLEM UDE/INDE
  # =================================================================

  # Freml√∏b FRA udedel (BT12) - P√• det varme r√∏r der g√•r op
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_supply_line_eb101_bt12
    style:
      top: 57.5%
      left: 72%

  # Retur TIL udedel (EB101-BT3) - P√• det kolde r√∏r der g√•r ned
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_return_line_eb101_bt3
    style:
      top: 57.5%
      left: 24%

  # --- PUMPE A: GP12 (Ladepumpe - Gr√∏n cirkel p√• diagram) ---
  - type: state-icon
    entity: binary_sensor.vvm_ladepumpe
    icon: mdi:pump
    style:
      top: 46.4%
      left: 21%
      opacity: 0.9
      transform: scale(1.2)
    card_mod:
      style: |
        state-badge {
          {% if is_state(config.entity, 'on') %} animation: spin 3s linear infinite; {% endif %}
        }
        @keyframes spin { 100% { transform: rotate(360deg); } }

  # --- PUMPE B: GP1 (Varmeb√¶rerpumpe - R√∏d cirkel p√• diagram) ---
  - type: state-icon
    entity: binary_sensor.vvm_500_pump_heating_medium_eb100_gp1
    icon: mdi:pump
    style:
      top: 46.4%
      left: 65%
      opacity: 0.9
      transform: scale(1.2)
    card_mod:
      style: |
        state-badge {
          {% if is_state(config.entity, 'on') %} animation: spin 3s linear infinite; {% endif %}
        }
        @keyframes spin { 100% { transform: rotate(360deg); } }

  # =================================================================
  # ZONE 3: VVM 500 TANK & VARMEKREDS (TOPPEN)
  # =================================================================

  # Indend√∏rstemperatur
  - type: state-label
    style:
      left: 33.5%
      top: 13.5%
      font-weight: bold
    entity: sensor.ws2900_v2_01_18_indoor_temperature
    title: Indend√∏rs temperatur

  # Placeres inde i VVM-tanken (midten) hvor varmelegemet sidder.
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_power_internal_add_heat
    style:
      top: 33%
      left: 42%
      text-align: right

  # Varmt vand
  - type: state-label
    style:
      left: 69.9%
      top: 22%
      font-weight: bold
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_hot_water_temp
    title: Varmt vand

  # Varmt Vand Indstilling
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_varmt_vand_indstilling
    style:
      top: 9%
      left: 68%

  # =================================================================
  # STYRING: VARMT VAND BOOST (Dropdown Menu)
  # =================================================================
  # Vi bruger 'custom:hui-element' til at inds√¶tte en interaktiv r√¶kke.
  - type: custom:hui-element
    card_type: entities
    entities:
      - entity: select.vvm_500_hot_water_boost
        name: "Luksus"
        icon: mdi:NONE
    style:
      top: 73%
      left: 43.5%
      width: 50%
      z-index: 200
    card_mod:
      style: |
        ha-card {
          background: transparent !important;
        }
        #states {
          # Fjerner un√∏dig luft (padding) inde i kortet
          padding: 0 !important;
        }

  # Varmt Vand Top (BT7)
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_hot_water_top_bt7
    style:
      top: 25%
      left: 42%
      text-align: right

  # Varmt Vand Ladning (BT6)
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_hot_water_charging_bt6
    style:
      top: 41%
      left: 42%
      text-align: right

  # Buffer Top (BT63)
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_add_heat_bt63
    style:
      top: 29%
      left: 86%
      text-align: right

  # Buffer Bund / Retur (BT3)
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_return_line_bt3
    style:
      top: 36%
      left: 86%
      text-align: right

  # Freml√∏b til Huset (BT2)
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_calculated_supply_climate_system_1
    style:
      top: 8.5%
      left: 45%
      text-align: center

  # Returl√∏b fra Huset (BT3)
  - type: state-label
    entity: sensor.vvm_500_return_line_bt3
    style:
      top: 6.5%
      left: 21%
      text-align: center

  # Background Image
  - type: image
    style:
      top: 50%
      left: 50%
      width: 70%
      mix-blend-mode: lighten
      filter: invert(1)
    image:
      media_content_id: media-source://image_upload/e863fd9bbff2dc1e258c7168909dc6a2
      media_content_type: image/png
      metadata:
        title: VVM500 Diagram.png
        thumbnail: /api/image/serve/e863fd9bbff2dc1e258c7168909dc6a2/256x256
        media_class: image
        navigateIds:
          - media_content_type: app
            media_content_id: media-source://image_upload
    title: Baggrundsbillede

sync_logs
content:
#!/bin/bash
set -euo pipefail
# premise: inotify listens for events (create) from media insertion,
# as a background process.
# If a new device is created in /media/$USER and it contains folder mca_logs sync logs

# create a lockfile based on user id
LOCKFILE="/tmp/usb_log_sync_$(id -u).lock"

# If the PID in the lockfile is not running anymore remove else see if its running
if [[ -e "$LOCKFILE" ]]; then
    
    if kill -0 "$(cat "$LOCKFILE" 2>/dev/null)" 2>/dev/null; then
        echo "Another instance is already running (PID $(cat "$LOCKFILE")). Exiting." >&2
        exit 1
    else
        echo "Removing stale lockfile from previous session..."
        rm -f "$LOCKFILE"
    fi
fi
# PID of current script
echo "$$" > "$LOCKFILE"

# Clean up on exit, terminare, interupt hangup 
trap 'rm -f "$LOCKFILE"; exit 0' INT TERM EXIT HUP
# hide executions 
#exec 1>/dev/null     
#exec 2>/dev/null


WATCHDIR="/media/$USER"

inotifywait -m -e create "$WATCHDIR" --format "%f" | while read DIR; do
    MOUNTPOINT="$WATCHDIR/$DIR"
    #echo $MOUNTPOINT
    # drive is detected before full mount so wait upto 3 seconds
	for i in {1..30}; do 
		# if newly inserted device has an mca_logs folder, trigger rsync    
		if [[ -d "$MOUNTPOINT/mca_logs" ]]; then
	# where the logs are, relative to where the script is. 
    SCRIPT_DIR="$(cd "$(dirname "${BASH_SOURCE[0]}")" && pwd)"
    src="${SCRIPT_DIR}/../../logs"
    dst="$MOUNTPOINT/mca_logs"
    cd $src
            find . -type f -mtime -30 -print0 | rsync -av --files-from=- --from0 . "$dst/"
    break
		   fi
		sleep 0.1
	done
done

#keep it anyway for future use.
#spawn process from mca.py on init
#import subprocess
#sync_script = os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), "../../resources/scripts/synch2.sh")
#subprocess.Popen([sync_script])

#!/bin/bash
GUM_VERSION=$(curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/charmbracelet/gum/releases/latest | jq -r '.tag_name' | tr -d 'v')
wget -q "https://github.com/charmbracelet/gum/releases/download/v${GUM_VERSION}/gum_${GUM_VERSION}_Linux_x86_64.tar.gz"
tar -xf "gum_${GUM_VERSION}_Linux_x86_64.tar.gz" -C /usr/local/bin "gum_${GUM_VERSION}_Linux_x86_64/gum"
mv "/usr/local/bin/gum_${GUM_VERSION}_Linux_x86_64/gum" "/usr/local/bin/gum"
rmdir "/usr/local/bin/gum_${GUM_VERSION}_Linux_x86_64"
rm "gum_${GUM_VERSION}_Linux_x86_64.tar.gz"

K9S_VERSION=$(curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/derailed/k9s/releases/latest | jq -r '.tag_name')
gum spin --title="Downloading K9s"  -- \
  wget -q "https://github.com/derailed/k9s/releases/download/${K9S_VERSION}/k9s_Linux_amd64.tar.gz"
tar -xf k9s_Linux_amd64.tar.gz -C /usr/local/bin/ k9s
rm k9s_Linux_amd64.tar.gz

FZF_VERSION=$(curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/junegunn/fzf/releases/latest | jq -r '.tag_name' | tr -d 'v')
wget -q "https://github.com/junegunn/fzf/releases/download/v${FZF_VERSION}/fzf-${FZF_VERSION}-linux_amd64.tar.gz"
gum spin --title="Downloading fzf" -- \
  tar -xf "fzf-${FZF_VERSION}-linux_amd64.tar.gz" -C /usr/local/bin/ fzf
rm "fzf-${FZF_VERSION}-linux_amd64.tar.gz"

gum spin --title="Downloading kubelogin" -- \
  az aks install-cli --only-show-errors
az login --identity --only-show-errors 1>/dev/null
az account list --query '[].name' -o tsv | fzf -1 --footer="Pick subscription" --height=10% | xargs az account set --sub
az aks list | jq -r 'map("-g \(.resourceGroup) -n \(.name)") | .[]' | \
  fzf -1 --footer="Pick cluster" --height=10% | \
  xargs az aks get-credentials --overwrite-existing --admin
kubelogin convert-kubeconfig -l azurecli

title: # tk_subtractive_blend_polygons.py
content:
# tk_subtractive_blend_polygons.py

import tkinter as tk
from PIL import Image, ImageDraw, ImageTk, ImageChops
import math

sz = 600

def center_coords(coords_list, sz):
    xs = [x for coords in coords_list for x, y in coords]
    ys = [y for coords in coords_list for x, y in coords]
    min_x, max_x = min(xs), max(xs)
    min_y, max_y = min(ys), max(ys)
    width = max_x - min_x
    height = max_y - min_y
    offset_x = (sz - width) / 2 - min_x
    offset_y = (sz - height) / 2 - min_y
    return [[(x + offset_x, y + offset_y) for x, y in coords] for coords in coords_list]

def srgb_from_linear(x):
    if x <= 0.0031308:
        return 12.92 * x
    return 1.055 * (x ** (1/2.4)) - 0.055

def linear_from_srgb(x):
    if x <= 0.04045:
        return x / 12.92
    return ((x + 0.055) / 1.055) ** 2.4

def channel_transmission(v_srgb, leak, gamma):
    v_lin = linear_from_srgb(v_srgb)
    t = leak + (1.0 - leak) * (v_lin ** gamma)
    return max(0.0, min(1.0, t))

def subtractive_blend(c1, c2,
                              leak1=(0.02, 0.20, 0.85),
                              gamma1=(1.6, 1.4, 1.0),
                              leak2=(0.85, 0.90, 0.02),
                              gamma2=(1.0, 1.0, 1.6)):
    r1, g1, b1 = [v/255.0 for v in c1[:3]]
    r2, g2, b2 = [v/255.0 for v in c2[:3]]

    t1_r = channel_transmission(r1, leak1[0], gamma1[0])
    t1_g = channel_transmission(g1, leak1[1], gamma1[1])
    t1_b = channel_transmission(b1, leak1[2], gamma1[2])

    t2_r = channel_transmission(r2, leak2[0], gamma2[0])
    t2_g = channel_transmission(g2, leak2[1], gamma2[1])
    t2_b = channel_transmission(b2, leak2[2], gamma2[2])

    t_r = t1_r * t2_r
    t_g = t1_g * t2_g
    t_b = t1_b * t2_b

    R = int(round(255 * srgb_from_linear(t_r)))
    G = int(round(255 * srgb_from_linear(t_g)))
    B = int(round(255 * srgb_from_linear(t_b)))

    A = max(c1[3], c2[3])
    return (R, G, B, A)

def composite_shapes(shapes, sz):
    result = Image.new("RGBA", (sz, sz), (255, 255, 255, 255))
    accumulated_mask = Image.new("L", (sz, sz), 0)
    accumulated_color = None

    for coords, color in shapes:
        layer = Image.new("RGBA", (sz, sz), (0, 0, 0, 0))
        ImageDraw.Draw(layer).polygon(coords, fill=color)
        mask = layer.split()[3]

        overlap = ImageChops.multiply(accumulated_mask, mask)
        only_new = ImageChops.subtract(mask, overlap)

        if accumulated_color:
            blended = subtractive_blend(accumulated_color, color)
            result.paste(blended, mask=overlap)

        result.paste(color, mask=only_new)

        accumulated_mask = ImageChops.add(accumulated_mask, mask)
        accumulated_color = color

    return result

# Example: two triangles
blue_coords = [(0, 0), (500, 0), (250, 450)]
cx = sum(x for x, y in blue_coords) / 3
cy = sum(y for x, y in blue_coords) / 3
theta = math.radians(30)
yellow_coords = []
for (x, y) in blue_coords:
    x_new = cx + (x - cx) * math.cos(theta) - (y - cy) * math.sin(theta)
    y_new = cy + (x - cx) * math.sin(theta) + (y - cy) * math.cos(theta)
    yellow_coords.append((x_new, y_new))

blue_coords, yellow_coords = center_coords([blue_coords, yellow_coords], sz)

shapes = [
    (blue_coords, (0, 0, 255, 255)),
    (yellow_coords, (255, 255, 0, 255)),
]

result = composite_shapes(shapes, sz)

root = tk.Tk()
root.geometry(f"{sz}x{sz}+0+0")
canvas = tk.Canvas(root, width=sz, height=sz, bg="white", highlightthickness=0)
canvas.pack()
tk_img = ImageTk.PhotoImage(result)
canvas.create_image(0, 0, anchor="nw", image=tk_img)
root.mainloop()

title: BIG TECH BLOCKER v2.2
content:
@echo off
setlocal enabledelayedexpansion
title Big Tech Blocker v2.2 - 50+ Domains + Backup!
color 0A
chcp 437 >nul 2>&1  REM Fix for ASCII graphics display
echo.
echo +======================================================+
echo ^| üõ°Ô∏è BIG TECH BLOCKER v2.2 - TOTAL CONTROL            ^|
echo ^| Akamai‚Ä¢Google‚Ä¢Meta‚Ä¢Amazon‚Ä¢Apple‚Ä¢MS‚Ä¢TikTok+50!        ^|
echo ^| WARNING: MS Block breaks GitHub/Logins!              ^|
echo +======================================================+
echo.
:: Admin Check
net session >nul 2>&1 || (echo [ERROR]üî¥ Run as ADMIN! & pause & exit /b)
:: AUTO-BACKUP
if not exist "Blocker_Backup" mkdir Blocker_Backup
set "backup_file=Blocker_Backup\firewall_%date:~-4,4%%date:~-10,2%%date:~-7,2%_%time:~0,2%%time:~3,2%.wfw"
netsh advfirewall export "%backup_file%" >nul 2>&1
if errorlevel 1 (echo [X] Backup failed! Check syntax or permissions.) else (echo [‚úì] Backup saved: %backup_file%!)
:: DNS Setup (Quad9 for speed/privacy)
echo [DNS] Using Quad9 (9.9.9.9) - Privacy + Malware Block!
set "dns1=9.9.9.9" & set "dns2=149.112.112.112"
for %%i in (Ethernet Wi-Fi "Local Area Connection" "Wireless Connection") do (
    netsh interface ip set dns "%%i" static !dns1! primary >nul 2>&1
    netsh interface ip add dns "%%i" !dns2! index=2 >nul 2>&1
)
ipconfig /flushdns >nul 2>&1
ping -n 1 %dns1% >nul 2>&1 && echo [‚úì] DNS: Quad9 Active! (Ping OK) || echo [‚ö†Ô∏è DNS Ping Failed - Check connection!]
:: Always Allow Web + Bypass Streaming
netsh advfirewall firewall delete rule name="AllowWeb*" >nul 2>&1
netsh advfirewall firewall add rule name="AllowWeb_OUT" dir=out action=allow protocol=TCP remoteport=80,443 >nul 2>&1
netsh advfirewall firewall add rule name="AllowWeb_IN" dir=in action=allow protocol=TCP localport=80,443 >nul 2>&1
netsh advfirewall firewall add rule name="BypassNetflix" dir=out action=allow remoteip=192.229.138.0/24,23.246.0.0/18 >nul 2>&1
netsh advfirewall firewall add rule name="BypassTwitch" dir=out action=allow remoteip=151.101.0.0/16 >nul 2>&1
echo [‚úì] Web + Netflix/Twitch Bypass Active!
:menu
echo.
echo +=================== MENU ===================+
echo ^| A.Akamai (CDN/Global)                     ^|
echo ^| 1.Google (YouTube/Ads) 6.TikTok           ^|
echo ^| 2.Meta (FB/Insta)      7.Snapchat         ^|
echo ^| 3.Amazon (AWS/Ads)     8.Uber/Lyft        ^|
echo ^| 4.Apple (iCloud)       9.Twitter/X        ^|
echo ^| 5.Microsoft* (GitHub!) 0.Telemetry        ^|
echo ^| B.Block All            U.Unblock All      ^|
echo ^| I.Import Rules                            ^|
echo ^| *CAUTION: Unblock MS first! E.Export      ^|
echo +============================= X.Exit ======+
set /p choice="Enter: "
if /i "!choice!"=="X" goto end
if /i "!choice!"=="E" (
    netsh advfirewall export "Blocker_Backup\current.wfw" >nul 2>&1
    if errorlevel 1 (echo [X] Export failed!) else (echo [‚úì] Rules Exported to current.wfw!)
    goto menu
)
if /i "!choice!"=="I" (
    echo [IMPORT] Finding latest backup...
    set "latest="
    for /f %%f in ('dir /b /od "Blocker_Backup\*.wfw" 2^>nul') do set latest=%%f
    if not defined latest (echo [X] No backups found!) else (
        netsh advfirewall import "Blocker_Backup\!latest!" >nul 2>&1
        if errorlevel 1 (echo [X] Import failed!) else (echo [‚úì] Imported: !latest!)
    )
    goto menu
)
if /i "!choice!"=="B" (set "toggle=B" & set "multi= A 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 0" & goto multi_process)
if /i "!choice!"=="U" (set "toggle=U" & set "multi= A 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 0" & goto multi_process)
:: Single choice handling
set "multi=!choice!"
:multi_process
for %%c in (!multi!) do (
    if "%%c"=="A" set "group=AKAMAI" & set "rules=Block_AKAMAI_" & set "domains=akamai.com akamai.net edgesuite.net edgekey.net akamaized.net akamaiedge.net akamaitechnologies.com akadns.net akaa.net akamaistream.net akamaicdn.net"
    if "%%c"=="1" set "group=GOOGLE" & set "rules=Block_GOOGLE_" & set "domains=google.com youtube.com googlevideo.com doubleclick.net google-analytics.com googlesyndication.com googleadservices.com android.com blogger.com gstatic.com googleapis.com ggpht.com ytimg.com"
    if "%%c"=="2" set "group=META" & set "rules=Block_META_" & set "domains=facebook.com fb.com fbcdn.net facebook.net fbsbx.com messenger.com instagram.com whatsapp.com whatsapp.net oculus.com connect.facebook.net graph.facebook.com"
    if "%%c"=="3" set "group=AMAZON" & set "rules=Block_AMAZON_" & set "domains=amazon.com amazonaws.com media-amazon.com ssl-images-amazon.com amazon-adsystem.com a2z.com images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com"
    if "%%c"=="4" set "group=APPLE" & set "rules=Block_APPLE_" & set "domains=apple.com icloud.com itunes.com aaplimg.com cdn-apple.com mzstatic.com apple-mapkit.com idmsa.apple.com"
    if "%%c"=="5" set "group=MICROSOFT" & set "rules=Block_MS_" & set "domains=microsoft.com windows.com live.com outlook.com office.com onedrive.com azure.com bing.com msn.com skype.com xbox.com windowsupdate.com msftncsi.com github.com"
    if "%%c"=="6" set "group=TIKTOK" & set "rules=Block_TIKTOK_" & set "domains=tiktok.com tiktokv.com byteoversea.com byteimg.com ttlivecdn.com musically.com"
    if "%%c"=="7" set "group=SNAPCHAT" & set "rules=Block_SNAP_" & set "domains=snapchat.com sc-cdn.net cf-st.sc-cdn.net"
    if "%%c"=="8" set "group=UBER" & set "rules=Block_UBER_" & set "domains=uber.com lyft.com ubereats.com"
    if "%%c"=="9" set "group=TWITTER" & set "rules=Block_X_" & set "domains=twitter.com x.com t.co twimg.com twittercdn.com"
    if "%%c"=="0" set "group=TELEMETRY" & set "rules=Block_TELEMETRY_" & set "domains=telemetry.urs.microsoft.com settings-win.data.microsoft.com vortex.data.microsoft.com watson.telemetry.microsoft.com sqm.telemetry.microsoft.com sls.update.microsoft.com ooboot.data.microsoft.com diagnostics.support.microsoft.com feedback.microsoft.com telemetry.microsoft.com"
    if not defined group (echo [X] Invalid choice: %%c & goto menu)
    if /i "!toggle!"=="U" (
        echo [üîì UNBLOCKING] !group!...
        for %%d in (!domains!) do netsh advfirewall firewall delete rule name="!rules!%%d*" >nul 2>&1
        echo [‚úì] !group! UNBLOCKED!
    ) else (
        echo [üîí BLOCKING] !group!...
        set /a count=0
        for %%d in (!domains!) do (
            netsh advfirewall firewall delete rule name="!rules!%%d*" >nul 2>&1
            for /f "tokens=2 delims= " %%a in ('nslookup %%d !dns1! 2^>nul ^| findstr "Address" ^| findstr "[0-9]"') do (
                set /a count+=1
                netsh advfirewall firewall add rule name="!rules!%%d_%%a" dir=out action=block remoteip=%%a >nul 2>&1
            )
        )
        echo [‚úì] !group! BLOCKED (^!count! IPs^)!
    )
    set "group="
)
:: Quick Test
ping -n 1 8.8.8.8 >nul 2>&1 && echo [üåê Internet OK!] || echo [‚ö†Ô∏è No Internet - Check DNS/Firewall!]
goto menu
:end
echo [üèÅ ALL CHANGES SAVED! Backup: Blocker_Backup\]
pause

-- Main Script Logic
local function getBall()
    local balls = Workspace:FindFirstChild("Balls")
    if balls then
        for _, ball in pairs(balls:GetChildren()) do
            if ball:IsA("Part") then
                return ball
            end
        end
    end
    return nil
end

local function getClosestPlayer()
    local closestPlayer = nil
    local shortestDistance = math.huge
    
    for _, plr in pairs(Players:GetPlayers()) do
        if plr ~= player and plr.Character then
            local distance = (rootPart.Position - plr.Character.HumanoidRootPart.Position).Magnitude
            if distance < shortestDistance then
                shortestDistance = distance
                closestPlayer = plr
            end
        end
    end
    
    return closestPlayer
end

local function parry()
    local ball = getBall()
    if ball then
        local distance = (ball.Position - rootPart.Position).Magnitude
        local accuracy = Settings.AutoParryLobby and Settings.LobbyParryAccuracy or Settings.ParryAccuracy
        
        if distance < 20 and math.random(1, 100) <= accuracy then
            -- Trigger parry action
            local tool = character:FindFirstChildOfClass("Tool")
            if tool then
                tool:Activate()
            end
        end
    end
end

-- Auto Collect Rewards
spawn(function()
    while wait(1) do
        if Settings.AutoCollectRewards then
            local rewards = Workspace:FindFirstChild("Rewards")
            if rewards then
                for _, reward in pairs(rewards:GetChildren()) do
                    if reward:IsA("Part") or reward:IsA("Model") then
                        rootPart.CFrame = reward.CFrame
                        wait(0.1)
                    end
                end
            end
        end
    end
end)

spawn(function()

            if playButton and playButton:IsA("TextButton") then
                firesignal(playButton.MouseButton1Click)
            end
        end
    end
end)

-- Auto Parry Loop
RunService.Heartbeat:Connect(function()
    if Settings.AutoParry or Settings.AutoParryLobby then
        parry()
    end
    
    if Settings.AutoSpam then
        local tool = character:FindFirstChildOfClass("Tool")
        if tool then
            tool:Activate()
        end
    end
    
    if Settings.NoClip then
        for _, part in pairs(character:GetDescendants()) do
            if part:IsA("BasePart") then
                part.CanCollide = false
            end
        end
    end
end)

-- Fly System
local flying = false
local flySpeed = 50
local bodyVelocity
local bodyGyro

local function startFly()
    flying = true
    bodyVelocity = Instance.new("BodyVelocity")
    bodyVelocity.MaxForce = Vector3.new(9e9, 9e9, 9e9)
    bodyVelocity.Velocity = Vector3.new(0, 0, 0)
    bodyVelocity.Parent = rootPart
    
    bodyGyro = Instance.new("BodyGyro")
    bodyGyro.MaxTorque = Vector3.new(9e9, 9e9, 9e9)
    bodyGyro.CFrame = rootPart.CFrame
    bodyGyro.Parent = rootPart
end

local function stopFly()
    flying = false
    if bodyVelocity then bodyVelocity:Destroy() end
    if bodyGyro then bodyGyro:Destroy() end
end

RunService.RenderStepped:Connect(function()
    if Settings.Fly and not flying then
        startFly()
    elseif not Settings.Fly and flying then
        stopFly()
    end
    
    if flying then
        local cam = Workspace.CurrentCamera
        local moveDirection = Vector3.new()
        
        if UserInputService:IsKeyDown(Enum.KeyCode.W) then
            moveDirection = moveDirection + (cam.CFrame.LookVector * flySpeed)
        end
        if UserInputService:IsKeyDown(Enum.KeyCode.S) then
            moveDirection = moveDirection - (cam.CFrame.LookVector * flySpeed)
        end
        if UserInputService:IsKeyDown(Enum.KeyCode.A) then
            moveDirection = moveDirection - (cam.CFrame.RightVector * flySpeed)
        end
        if UserInputService:IsKeyDown(Enum.KeyCode.D) then
            moveDirection = moveDirection + (cam.CFrame.RightVector * flySpeed)
        end
        if UserInputService:IsKeyDown(Enum.KeyCode.Space) then
            moveDirection = moveDirection + Vector3.new(0, flySpeed, 0)
        end
        if UserInputService:IsKeyDown(Enum.KeyCode.LeftShift) then
            moveDirection = moveDirection - Vector3.new(0, flySpeed, 0)
        end
        
        bodyVelocity.Velocity = moveDirection
        bodyGyro.CFrame = cam.CFrame
    end
end)

-- ESP System
local espObjects = {}

local function createESP(target)
    if not target or not target:FindFirstChild("HumanoidRootPart") then return end
    
    local esp = {
        Target = target,
        Box = nil,
        Tracer = nil,
        Name = nil
    }
    
    if Settings.ESPBoxes then
        local box = Drawing.new("Square")
        box.Visible = true
        box.Color = Settings.ESPColor
        box.Thickness = 2
        box.Transparency = 1
        box.Filled = false
        esp.Box = box
    end
    
    if Settings.ESPTracers then
        local tracer = Drawing.new("Line")
        tracer.Visible = true
        tracer.Color = Settings.ESPColor
        tracer.Thickness = 1
        tracer.Transparency = 1
        esp.Tracer = tracer
    end
    
    if Settings.ESPNames then
        local name = Drawing.new("Text")
        name.Visible = true
        name.Color = Settings.ESPColor
        name.Size = 18
        name.Center = true
        name.Outline = true
        name.Text = target.Name
        esp.Name = name
    end
    
    table.insert(espObjects, esp)
end

local function updateESP()
    for _, esp in pairs(espObjects) do
        if esp.Box then esp.Box:Remove() end
        if esp.Tracer then esp.Tracer:Remove() end
        if esp.Name then esp.Name:Remove() end
    end
    espObjects = {}
    
    if Settings.EnableESP then
        for _, plr in pairs(Players:GetPlayers()) do
            if plr ~= player and plr.Character then
                createESP(plr.Character)
            end
        end
    end
end

RunService.RenderStepped:Connect(function()
    if Settings.EnableESP then
        updateESP()
    end
end)
